      2: "Why option C is CORRECT - Filing a financing statement (UCC-1) with the appropriate state office is the most common method for perfecting a security interest in goods because it provides public notice to other creditors that the secured party has a claim against the debtor's collateral.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Taking physical possession of the debtor's *home* is not a method for perfecting a security interest in *goods* under UCC Article 9. Possession as a method of perfection applies to the specific goods serving as collateral, not the debtor's residence.",
