    educational: "Perfection is the process by which a secured party puts the world on notice of its security interest in the debtor's collateral. This is crucial for establishing priority over other creditors who may also have claims against the same collateral. Without perfection, a secured party's claim may be subordinate to other creditors, especially in bankruptcy.",
    examTip: "Remember that filing a financing statement is the most common perfection method, but don't forget the exceptions like possession and automatic perfection for PMSIs in consumer goods.",
    memoryAid: "Think of 'Filing First' - Filing a financing statement is usually the first step to protect your interest.",
