    explanation: "IRC §1091: Loss on sale of stock/securities is disallowed if taxpayer purchases substantially identical securities within 30 days before or after the sale (a 61-day window: 30 days before + sale date + 30 days after). The disallowed loss is added to the basis of the replacement securities. Holding period of the old securities tacks onto the new securities. \"Substantially identical\": same company's stock (buying Microsoft and selling Microsoft); options or contracts to acquire are included. Does NOT apply to gains. Does NOT apply to different companies or different types of securities (e.g., selling stock, buying bonds of same company — generally not identical).",
