    explanation: "Three types of recording statutes: (1) Race — whoever records first wins (regardless of notice; rare), (2) Notice — subsequent BFP without notice prevails (even without recording; recording protects against later parties), (3) Race-Notice (most common) — subsequent purchaser must BOTH: (a) take without notice (actual, constructive, inquiry) AND (b) record before the prior interest. Notice types: actual (direct knowledge), constructive (recorded documents in chain of title), inquiry (facts suggesting a reasonable buyer should investigate).",
