    explanation: "Circular 230 §10.34: A practitioner must not sign a return with a position unless: (1) the position has a reasonable basis (lowest standard) AND (2) if the position is an undisclosed position: the practitioner reasonably believes it is more likely than not (>50%) to be sustained on its merits. For disclosed positions (Form 8275/8275-R): the reasonable basis standard alone applies (lower threshold). The practitioner also cannot advise a client to take a frivolous position. Standards hierarchy: frivolous < reasonable basis < realistic possibility < substantial authority < more likely than not.",
