    explanation: "LLC advantages: (1) Limited liability — members' personal assets protected (like a corporation), (2) Flexible management — member-managed or manager-managed, (3) Tax flexibility — default: single-member = disregarded entity (Schedule C), multi-member = partnership; can elect S corp or C corp treatment. (4) No ownership restrictions (unlike S corps). (5) No requirement for formalities like corporate minutes/resolutions. Formed by filing Articles of Organization with the state. Operating Agreement governs internal affairs. Piercing the \"veil\" is possible (but less common than corporate veil-piercing).",
