    explanation: "IRC §25A(i) AOTC: $2,500 maximum per student (100% of first $2,000 + 25% of next $2,000). Requirements: (1) First four years of postsecondary education, (2) Enrolled at least half-time, (3) Pursuing a degree, (4) No felony drug conviction. 40% refundable ($1,000 max refund per student). MAGI phase-out: $80K-$90K (single), $160K-$180K (MFJ). Qualified expenses: tuition, fees, required course materials (books, supplies). Cannot claim for same student in same year as Lifetime Learning Credit. Course materials qualify for AOTC but NOT for LLC.",
