    correctAnswer: 3,
    explanation: "IRC §223 HSA \"triple tax advantage\": (1) Contributions are deductible (for AGI / above-the-line), (2) Earnings grow tax-free, (3) Distributions for qualified medical expenses are tax-free. Requirements: must be covered by a High Deductible Health Plan (HDHP), no other non-HDHP coverage, not enrolled in Medicare, not claimed as a dependent. 2024 limits: $4,150 (self-only), $8,300 (family), $1,000 catch-up (55+). Funds roll over annually (no \"use it or lose it\" like FSAs). After age 65, non-medical withdrawals are taxed as ordinary income (no 20% penalty). HSAs are portable — owned by the individual.",
