    explanation: "The dividends received deduction (DRD) under §243 depends on the ownership percentage: (1) less than 20% ownership → 50% DRD; (2) 20% to less than 80% ownership → 65% DRD; (3) 80% or more ownership (affiliated group member) → 100% DRD. Since Corp A owns 25% (between 20% and 80%), the DRD is 65%, resulting in a $65,000 deduction ($100,000 × 65%). The DRD is generally limited to the applicable percentage of taxable income (before DRD, NOL deduction, and capital loss carryback), unless the DRD creates or increases a net operating loss. This limitation prevents the DRD from creating artificial losses.",
