    explanation: "The accumulated earnings tax (§531-537) is a penalty tax designed to discourage corporations from accumulating earnings to avoid shareholder-level dividend taxes: (1) imposed at 20% on \"accumulated taxable income\" (taxable income minus income taxes, charitable contributions in excess of the 10% limit, certain adjustments, dividends paid, and the accumulated earnings credit); (2) the accumulated earnings credit is the greater of: (a) $250,000 ($150,000 for personal service corporations) minus accumulated E&P at the beginning of the year, or (b) the amount of E&P retained for reasonable business needs; (3) \"reasonable needs\" include business expansion, debt retirement, working capital needs (Bardahl formula), investments, or contingencies; (4) the tax applies only when the purpose of the accumulation is to avoid dividend tax — mere accumulation without tax-avoidance purpose is not penalized.",
