    explanation: "Under §302(b)(2), a substantially disproportionate redemption must meet THREE tests: (1) the shareholder's post-redemption voting stock ownership must be less than 80% of the pre-redemption percentage (ratio test); (2) the shareholder must own less than 50% of the total combined voting power after the redemption; (3) the redemption must not be essentially equivalent to a dividend. Example: If a shareholder owns 60% before redemption, the shareholder must own less than 48% (60% × 80%) after redemption AND less than 50% of total voting power. Constructive ownership rules under §318 apply (family attribution, entity attribution). Other qualifying redemptions: §302(b)(1) \"not essentially equivalent to a dividend,\" §302(b)(3) complete termination, §302(b)(4) partial liquidation.",
