    explanation: "In a §351 exchange with boot: (1) Gain realized = FMV received ($90,000 stock + $10,000 cash = $100,000) minus basis transferred ($60,000) = $40,000; (2) Gain recognized = lesser of gain realized ($40,000) or boot received ($10,000) = $10,000; (3) Stock basis = transferor's basis in property transferred ($60,000) + gain recognized ($10,000) - boot received ($10,000) - FMV of boot (already netted) = $60,000. Formula: Stock basis = transferred basis + gain recognized - boot received. The corporation's basis in the property = transferor's basis ($60,000) + gain recognized by transferor ($10,000) = $70,000 (§362(a)). Losses are NEVER recognized in a §351 exchange.",
