    explanation: "Under §741, the sale of a partnership interest produces capital gain or loss, BUT §751(a) requires recharacterization to ordinary income to the extent of \"hot assets\": (1) Hot assets include: (a) unrealized receivables — accounts receivable of a cash-basis partnership, §1245/§1250 recapture potential, and other items that would produce ordinary income if collected; (b) substantially appreciated inventory — inventory items with FMV exceeding 120% of the partnership's basis in the inventory; (2) the portion of gain attributable to the selling partner's share of hot assets is ordinary income; (3) the remaining gain is capital; (4) the amount realized includes the buyer's assumption of the selling partner's share of partnership liabilities (§752(d)); (5) if a §754 election is in effect, the partnership adjusts the inside basis of its assets under §743(b) to reflect the transferee's purchase price.",
