      2: "Why option C is WRONG - The sale of a partnership interest is a taxable event, resulting in either a gain or a loss. It is not tax-free.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - While the sale generally results in capital gain or loss, it's not always long-term capital gain. The holding period of the partnership interest determines whether it's long-term or short-term, and the presence of hot assets creates ordinary income.",
