      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Operating expenses are ordinary and necessary expenses incurred in running the business and are deducted from gross profit to arrive at ordinary business income.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Gross receipts represent the total revenue generated by the S corporation's business activities and are a key component in calculating ordinary business income.",
