      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - Form 1023 (or Form 1023-EZ for eligible smaller organizations) is the application form specifically used to apply for recognition of tax-exempt status under IRC §501(c)(3). It provides the IRS with detailed information about the organization's purpose, activities, and financial structure.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Form 1120 is the U.S. Corporation Income Tax Return, used by for-profit corporations to report their income, deductions, and calculate their income tax liability; it is not used by organizations seeking tax-exempt status.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Form SS-4 is an Application for Employer Identification Number (EIN), used to obtain an EIN from the IRS; while a tax-exempt organization will likely need an EIN, this form does not apply for tax-exempt status.",
