    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under IRC §482, the IRS has authority to allocate income, deductions, credits, and allowances among two or more organizations, trades, or businesses owned or controlled by the same interests if necessary to clearly reflect income or prevent tax evasion. The arm's length standard is the benchmark — transactions between related parties must be priced as if they occurred between unrelated parties dealing at arm's length. Transfer pricing methods include: comparable uncontrolled price (CUP), resale price, cost plus, comparable profits method (CPM), and profit split. Penalties of 20-40% apply for substantial/gross transfer pricing misstatements.",
