    options: ["$450,000","$300,000 (the old basis carries over since gain is partially deferred)","$250,000","$350,000"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "In a like-kind exchange with boot: (1) Realized gain = $500,000 − $300,000 = $200,000. (2) Recognized gain = lesser of boot ($50,000) or realized gain ($200,000) = $50,000. (3) Basis in new property = adjusted basis of old property − boot received + gain recognized = $300,000 − $50,000 + $50,000 = $300,000. Alternatively: FMV of new property − deferred gain = $450,000 − $150,000 = $300,000. The deferred gain of $150,000 is preserved in the lower basis of the replacement property.",
