    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under IRC §1033(g), for real property held for productive use in a trade or business or for investment that is condemned (or sold under threat of condemnation), the replacement standard is the broader \"like-kind\" standard of §1031, rather than the narrower \"similar or related in service or use\" test. This means any real property of a like kind qualifies (e.g., a condemned office building could be replaced with raw land). For casualties, thefts, and other involuntary conversions, the narrower \"similar or related in service or use\" standard applies under the general §1033 rules and requires a closer functional match.",
