      2: "C) Identical property only is WRONG because the replacement property does not need to be identical. Both the 'similar or related in service or use' and 'like-kind' standards allow for replacement with different, but functionally or legally similar, property.",
      3: "D) Any property of equal value is WRONG because while the replacement property must generally be of equal or greater value to fully defer the gain, it must also meet either the 'similar or related in service or use' or 'like-kind' standard, depending on the type of involuntary conversion.",
