    explanation: "Under IRC §465, the amount at risk includes: (1) cash contributed, (2) adjusted basis of property contributed, (3) amounts borrowed for which the taxpayer is personally liable (recourse debt), and (4) amounts borrowed secured by property NOT used in the activity. Nonrecourse financing is generally NOT included in the at-risk amount, except for qualified nonrecourse financing secured by real property used in the activity (from qualified lenders or government entities). Losses deductible are limited to the amount at risk; excess losses are suspended and carried forward.",
