    question: "In a reverse like-kind exchange, the replacement property is acquired before the relinquished property is transferred. This is permitted if:",
    options: ["Both properties are exchanged on the same day","A qualified exchange accommodation arrangement (QEAA) is used, and the parked property is transferred within 180 days","The buyer agrees to hold the property for the taxpayer","Reverse exchanges are not permitted under any circumstances"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under Revenue Procedure 2000-37, a reverse exchange is permitted through a Qualified Exchange Accommodation Arrangement (QEAA). An exchange accommodation titleholder (EAT) acquires and \"parks\" either the replacement property or the relinquished property. The taxpayer must identify the relinquished property within 45 days of the EAT acquiring the replacement property, and the exchange must be completed within 180 days. The EAT must hold the property under a written agreement, and the taxpayer cannot have owned the parked property at any time during the arrangement. This safe harbor eliminates the risk of the IRS challenging the exchange.",
