    explanation: "Under IRC §469(g)(1), when a taxpayer makes a fully taxable disposition of an entire interest in a passive activity, all previously suspended passive activity losses from that activity are released and may be deducted in full against any type of income (ordinary, capital, passive, or nonpassive). The losses are first applied against net income or loss from the activity in the year of disposition, then against net income or loss from all other passive activities, and finally against nonpassive income. A \"fully taxable\" disposition means the entire interest is disposed of in a transaction where gain or loss is fully recognized (not a gift, related party sale under §267, or installment sale).",
