    explanation: "Under IRC §318(a), stock ownership is attributed from/to: (1) FAMILY — spouse, children, grandchildren, and parents (NOT siblings, aunts, uncles, or cousins); (2) PARTNERSHIPS — proportionate attribution between partner and partnership; (3) ESTATES/TRUSTS — beneficiary owns proportionate share, and entity owns beneficiary's share; (4) CORPORATIONS — attribution from 50%+ shareholders to corporation and from corporation to 50%+ shareholders (proportionate). The §318 rules apply for purposes of stock redemptions (§302), constructive dividends (§304), controlled groups (§1563), and other provisions. Note: §267 (related party loss disallowance) uses DIFFERENT attribution rules that include siblings.",
