    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under IRC §453(i), all depreciation recapture (§1245 and §1250) must be recognized in full in the year of sale, even if the installment method is used for the remaining gain. The recapture amount is added to the selling price payments received in the year of sale for purposes of computing gain. Only the §1231 gain (gain in excess of recapture) can be reported on the installment method. Example: if a machine sold for $100,000 has $40,000 of §1245 recapture and $20,000 of §1231 gain, the $40,000 recapture is fully recognized in year 1, while the $20,000 §1231 gain is spread over the installment period.",
