      2: "Why option C is WRONG - The recapture is not deferred; the tax code specifically requires immediate recognition in the year of the sale, not when the final payment is received.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Section 1245 recapture is treated as ordinary income, not capital gain. It represents the portion of the gain that offsets prior depreciation deductions.",
