    explanation: "Under IRC §165(g), if a security (stock or bond) becomes completely worthless during the taxable year, the loss is treated as a capital loss deemed to occur on the LAST DAY of the taxable year. This timing rule matters for determining whether the loss is short-term or long-term based on the holding period. The taxpayer must demonstrate that the security became completely worthless during the year (partial worthlessness is generally not deductible for securities). A special 7-year statute of limitations applies for refund claims related to worthless securities (§6511(d)(1)).",
