      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Casualty losses typically involve sudden, unexpected events like natural disasters or accidents that damage or destroy property. A security becoming worthless is not considered a casualty.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - While personal losses are often nondeductible, a loss on a worthless security is generally deductible, but only as a capital loss, subject to capital loss limitations.",
