    educational: "Understanding the difference between capital and ordinary losses is crucial. Capital losses are subject to limitations on deductibility (currently $3,000 per year with a carryforward), while ordinary losses can generally offset ordinary income without such limitations. The 'deemed sale' at year-end simplifies record-keeping and ensures consistent treatment.",
    examTip: "Remember the 'last day of the year' rule for worthless securities; it's a frequently tested detail. Pay attention to whether the question asks about the *type* of loss (capital) or the *timing* of the loss (last day of the year).",
