    explanation: "Under IRC §465(b)(6), qualified nonrecourse financing is an exception to the general rule that nonrecourse debt is excluded from the at-risk amount. To qualify: (1) the financing must be secured by real property used in the activity, (2) the lender must be a \"qualified person\" — a bank, savings institution, government entity, or person regularly engaged in the lending business (excluding the seller or a person related to the seller), (3) no person may be personally liable for repayment. This exception ensures that typical commercial real estate lending (mortgages on real property from institutional lenders) is included in the at-risk amount.",
