      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Financing from a related party generally does not qualify as qualified nonrecourse financing because it lacks the arm's-length nature required to ensure the taxpayer is truly at risk.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Qualified nonrecourse financing must be secured by real property used in the activity; unsecured financing, even from a commercial bank, does not meet the requirements.",
