    explanation: "Accumulated taxable income = accumulated earnings − reasonable business needs − accumulated earnings credit. But more precisely: the tax applies to current year's accumulated taxable income, not total accumulated earnings. The excess = $2,800,000 − $1,200,000 (reasonable needs) − $250,000 (minimum credit) = $1,350,000. The 20% accumulated earnings tax would be $270,000. The credit is the greater of $250,000 or the amount needed for reasonable business needs.",
