      2: "Option C is WRONG because agents *can* modify contract terms if they have the authority to do so, whether express, implied, or apparent.",
      3: "Option D is WRONG because while apparent authority exists when a principal leads a third party to believe an agent has authority, a significant discount outside customary practice may not be considered reasonable reliance.",
