      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - To be a holder in due course (HDC), you must give value for the instrument, act in good faith (honestly), and have no knowledge of any problems with the instrument (e.g., it's overdue, there's a claim against it, or it's been dishonored). This protects the HDC from certain defenses the issuer might have.",
