      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - This option accurately reflects the core requirements for innocent spouse relief under §6015(b): an understatement of tax attributable to the other spouse's erroneous items, the requesting spouse's lack of knowledge (or reason to know) of the understatement, and the inequity of holding the requesting spouse liable.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Filing a joint return by mistake is not a basis for innocent spouse relief. The return must have been filed jointly knowingly, but the spouse seeking relief was unaware of the erroneous items.",
