      1: "Option B is WRONG because partial performance only makes the contract enforceable to the extent of the performance; it doesn't remove the entire contract from the Statute of Frauds.",
      2: "Option C is WRONG because while the Statute of Frauds generally requires contracts for the sale of goods over $500 to be in writing, there are exceptions, including partial performance.",
