    educational: "The IRS audit process includes opportunities for taxpayers to resolve disputes administratively before resorting to litigation. A 30-day letter allows taxpayers to request a conference with the IRS Appeals Office, offering a chance to negotiate a settlement.",
    examTip: "Remember the sequence of events in the IRS audit process. A 30-day letter precedes a 90-day letter (notice of deficiency). Appealing within the IRS is generally preferable to going straight to court.",
