    examTip: "Remember that disclosure of a position does not automatically protect a tax preparer from penalties if the position is deemed unreasonable. Always consider whether there is substantial authority for a tax position before including it on a return.",
    memoryAid: "Think of 'RID' - Reasonable, Income, Disclosure, when considering preparer penalties. Was the position reasonable? What was the income derived by the preparer? Was the position disclosed?",
