    educational: "Attachment is the process by which a security interest becomes enforceable against the debtor. Perfection is the process by which a security interest becomes effective against third parties. Attachment is necessary before perfection can occur.",
    examTip: "Remember the three requirements for attachment: value, debtor's rights, and security agreement (authenticated or possession/control by secured party).  Don't confuse attachment with perfection.",
    memoryAid: "Think of attachment as 'VAD': Value, Agreement, Debtor's rights.",
