    question: "During 2023, Beta Corporation, a calendar-year taxpayer, incurred the following expenses in connection with the creation of the corporation:\n\n*   Legal fees for drafting the corporate charter: $15,000\n*   Commissions paid to underwriters: $60,000\n*   Expenses of temporary directors: $10,000\n\nAssuming Beta Corporation began active business operations on July 1, 2023, what is the maximum amount Beta Corporation can deduct for organizational expenditures and start-up costs in 2023?",
