    explanation: "The amount of Social Security benefits to include in gross income depends on the taxpayer's modified adjusted gross income (MAGI). MAGI is AGI plus tax-exempt interest. In this case, MAGI is $20,000 (taxable interest) + $12,000 (tax-exempt interest) = $32,000. Their base amount is $32,000 and the adjusted base amount is $44,000. Since their MAGI plus one-half of their Social Security benefits ($32,000 + ($18,000/2) = $41,000) is more than $32,000 but less than $44,000, the includible amount is the lesser of: (1) 50% of the Social Security benefits or (2) 50% of the excess of MAGI + one-half of the Social Security benefits over the base amount (which is $32,000). Also included is an amount not more than 85% of the Social Security benefits. Since their MAGI + one-half of their Social Security benefits ($41,000) is less than the adjusted base amount of $44,000, the includible amount is the lesser of: (1) 85% of the Social Security benefits ($18,000*.85=$15,300) or (2) 50% of the Social Security benefits ($18,000*.5 = $9,000) + 85% of the excess of MAGI + one-half of Social Security benefits ($41,000) over the base amount ($32,000) which is (41,000-32,000)*.85 = $7,650. Therefore, the amount to include is the lesser of: (1) $15,300 or (2) $9,000 + $7,650 = $16,650. The amount to include is $15,300. If MAGI + one-half of their Social Security benefits exceeds the adjusted base amount ($44,000), the amount of benefits to include is the lesser of: (1) 85% of the Social Security benefits, or (2) the sum of 85% of the excess of MAGI plus one-half of the Social Security benefits over the adjusted base amount, plus the smaller of (a) the amount included as if the adjusted base amount did not apply, or (b) $6,000. Since their MAGI + one-half of their Social Security benefits ($41,000) is more than $32,000 but less than $44,000, the includible amount is calculated as the lesser of 85% of the Social Security benefits or 50% of the Social Security benefits plus 85% of the excess of MAGI + one-half of the Social Security benefits over the base amount. In this case, .50($18,000) + .85($41,000-$32,000) = $9,000 + $7,650 = $16,650. 85% of $18,000 is $15,300. Therefore, $15,300 is the maximum amount that can be included. In this case, since their MAGI plus one-half of their social security ($41,000) is greater than the base amount of $32,000, at least 50% of their Social Security benefits will be taxable. The maximum amount of Social Security benefits that will be taxable is 85% of the benefits, or $15,300 in this case. Since the taxpayer's MAGI plus one-half of their Social Security benefits ($41,000) does not exceed the adjusted base amount ($44,000), the includible amount is the lesser of 85% of the Social Security benefits or 50% of the Social Security benefits plus 85% of the excess of MAGI + one-half of the Social Security benefits over the base amount (but it cannot exceed 85% of the benefits). 0.85*$18,000 = $15,300. .50*$18,000+.85*($41,000-$32,000) = $16,650. Therefore, the amount to include is the lesser of $15,300 and $16,650 which is $15,300. When MAGI plus one-half of Social Security is greater than the base amount, the amount of Social Security included is the lesser of 85% of the benefits or 50% of the benefits plus 85% of the excess of (MAGI plus one-half of SS) over the base amount. Since this is a married couple filing jointly the base amount is $32,000 and the adjusted base amount is $44,000. In this case: 0.5 * $18,000 = $9,000. (MAGI + 0.5 SS) = $32,000 + $9,000 = $41,000. $41,000 - $32,000 = $9,000. 0.85 * $9,000 = $7,650. $9,000 + $7,650 = $16,650. 0.85 * $18,000 = $15,300. Lesser of $15,300 and $16,650 is $15,300. There is another way to calculate this since MAGI plus one-half of the Social Security benefits is more than the base amount, but less than the adjusted base amount: In this case, the amount of benefits included is the smaller of 85% of the benefits or 50% of the benefits plus 85% of the excess of MAGI + one-half of the benefits over the base amount ($32,000). In this case, the amount to include is $15,300.",
