    options: ["MegaCorp can recover the $5,000 in consequential damages because TinyCo's limitation of liability was a material alteration and not expressly agreed to.","MegaCorp cannot recover the $5,000 in consequential damages because TinyCo's limitation of liability became part of the contract since MegaCorp did not object to it within a reasonable time.","MegaCorp can recover the $5,000 in consequential damages because limitations on consequential damages are unconscionable in all commercial transactions.","MegaCorp cannot recover the $5,000 in consequential damages because the UCC requires all limitations of liability to be conspicuously displayed, and there is no evidence of that here."],
