    examTip: "Focus on whether the acceptance was expressly conditional and whether the additional terms materially alter the original agreement. Look for language that indicates a clear unwillingness to proceed without the new terms.",
    memoryAid: "Remember the acronym \"MAC\" for Material Alteration, Offer limited, and Communication of objection. If any of these are present, the additional terms do not become part of the contract.",
